Former Senate Leader, Victor Ndoma Egba, is bereaved. His wife Amaka died in a fatal accident along Benin-Akure road on Friday. Egba confirmed her demise to Blueprint in Calabar. Amaka was reportedly going for a function in Akure, Ondo State. The Cross River politician has lost three relatives within a few months. Between June and August, his mother-in-law, his own mother and media aide died. His residence was attacked in late October by hoodlums after the End SARS protest went awry.